### Arrays

An array is a collection of elements stored in contiguous memory locations. Each element can be accessed directly by its index. However, accessing an element by its key (like a dictionary) requires a linear search through the array, which results in \(O(n)\) time complexity.

#### Example: Linear Search in an Array of Dictionaries

